{"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PatternSpecProtocol"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Matches a string against a compiled pattern."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"match","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"stringLength","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"string","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"stringReversed","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">? = nil) -> "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Passing the correct"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"length of the string given is mandatory. The reversed string can be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"omitted by passing "},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", this is more efficient if the reversed"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"version of the string to be matched is not at hand, as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.PatternSpec.match","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] will only construct it if the compiled pattern"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"requires reverse matches."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that, if the user code will (possibly) match a string against a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"multitude of patterns containing wildcards, chances are high that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"some patterns will require a reversed string. In this case, it’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"more efficient to provide the reversed string to avoid multiple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"constructions thereof in the various calls to [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.PatternSpec.match"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note also that the reverse of a UTF-8 encoded string can in general"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not be obtained by [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.strreverse","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]. This works only if the string","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"does not contain any multibyte characters. GLib offers the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.utf8_strreverse","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] function to reverse UTF-8 encoded strings.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/patternspecprotocol\/match(stringlength:string:stringreversed:)"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PatternSpecProtocol\/match(stringLength:string:stringReversed:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"match"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"stringLength","kind":"externalParam"},{"text"